What happened in the Democratic Republic of the Congo
In 2010 a tanker crossed the village of Sange in the east of the DR Congo, tipping around and exploded. 230 people died.
After the civil war Africa's second largest country has been neglected for years and devastated. the roads in the region have become dangerous paths full of potholes that were difficult to navigate.
