A blog with the name untranslatable (e. g. insurmountable) tries to offer language enthusiasts a selection of words from all over the world that are difficult or at all difficult to translate.
There are such words in every language: they express certain situations or feelings that are often very complex or specific.
Some of these invaluable words are already well known today (like the famous Portuguese saudade) and others deeply rooted in a special culture (for example the Spanish sobrekah).
But all stubbornly resist every attempt of a simple translation.
One word or expression is not enough, which is why a full explanation and sometimes some context is required to understand exactly what is meant by this one word.
These unique words have been collected for quite a while in an online list.
Most of these lists cover Japanese, German, French, Portuguese or Finnish words while the author and linguist of "untranslatable" Steven Bird chose to focus on small languages.
