In one night in the autumn of 1994 the conquest of Afghanistan began by the Taliban.
Two years before, a terrible civil war broke out between the various Mujahedin groupings that had defeated the short-lived pro-Soviet government. thus Afghanistan has become a country of terror and despair.
At that time, Asharaf Barati, a 13-year-old boy who belongs to the ethnic group of Hazara, sat in Ghazni Province in central Afghanistan for the last time with his family at dinner.
Even if his mother did not say so at that time, she knew that she would not see her son for a long time - maybe even more.
In the morning, the boy should break up.
His uncle would fetch him and bring him to the tugs.
The city of Ghazni in Afghanistan.
